## Fumadocs MDX Component Guidelines

### Callout Component

Use the Callout component for highlighting important information instead of blockquotes (>). 

Syntax example:
```tsx
<Callout type="info" title="Optional Title">
  Content of the callout goes here.
</Callout>
```

Available types:
- `info` (default) - For general information and tips
- `warn` - For warnings and potential issues
- `error` - For critical information or errors

Example usage:
```tsx
<Callout type="warn" title="API Key Required">
  You need to obtain an API key before using this feature. Sign up for a free account to get your API key.
</Callout>
```

### Other Fumadocs Components

- **Card**: For creating linked cards in documentation
- **CodeBlock**: For adding formatted code examples with highlighting
- **Heading**: For creating customized section headers

For more details on available components, refer to the Fumadocs documentation at https://fumadocs.vercel.app/docs/ui/mdx
